Utterances.UttText: Subjective: Gerry Cage is a 46 yo M who presents to clinic with cc of sudden onset 7/10 non-radiating mid-sternal CP with associated lightheadedness in the setting of exertion.

Phrases.PhraseText: with cc of sudden onset 7/10 non-radiating mid-sternal CP
with associated lightheadedness in the setting of exertion.

Utterances.UttText: Gerry describes that he was carrying several heavy groceries the other day while shopping and recalls that he developed " a deep and heavy ache in the center of my chest" while walking to his car.

Phrases.PhraseText: heavy ache in the center of my chest"

Utterances.UttText: He notes that he put the groceries down at the time and sat next to his car for 5-10 minutes with full relief of symptoms.
He recalls hx of similar sx's in the setting of exertion, but notes that the pain was not as bad during those episodes.
Gerry denies SOB, palpitations, dizziness, or diaphoresis.
He also notes similar pain in chest following heavy lunch meals.

-Medications: Chlorthalidone (25 mg once a day by mouth) and Lisinopril (10 mg once per day by mouth) -Allergies: None -PMHx: HTN -PSHx: None -Social: +EtOH (2-3 glasses of wine on weekends), +Tobacco (1 PPD for 20 years), -Illicit Drugs -Family: Mother, decreased (DMII, HTN, Pulmonary Embolism), Father (MI at age 40, CABG), maternal grandmother (breast cancer)  Objective:  VS: 98F, 150/97 mmHg, HR of 85, RR of 14 General: Middle aged man in NAD.

Pulm: LCTAB  Labs: CBC, BMP, Troponin  Assessment: Gerry Cage is a 46 yo M with PMHx significant for HTN and early onset CVD in his father who presents with progressively worsening episodes of CP in the setting of exertion.

Utterances.UttText: Most likely stable angina given onset of symptoms with exertion and resolution with rest.
